= TTF_RenderGlyph_Solid =

Create an 8-bit palettized surface and render the given glyph at fast quality with the given font and color.

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_Surface * TTF_RenderGlyph_Solid(TTF_Font *font,
                    Uint16 ch, SDL_Color fg);
</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''font'''
|[[TTF_Font]] handle
|-
|'''ch'''
|character index
|-
|'''fg'''
|foreground color
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

== Remarks ==

The 0 pixel is the colorkey, giving a transparent background, and the 1
pixel is set to the text color. The glyph is rendered without any padding
or centering in the X direction, and aligned normally in the Y direction.
This function returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

